Subject: [PATCH 3/4] fix(error-handling): make codebase-review failures
 visible by default
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The `notify` job emitted a `::warning::` annotation that nobody sees
unless they navigate to the run page — directly violating the
checklist's CI/CD bullet ("All scheduled cron workflows notify the
team on failure"). Two additional gaps:
  - `needs:` listed only `[review, fix]`, so `determine-area` failures
    propagated as `skipped` (not `failure`) and bypassed the alert.
  - The condition checked only `'failure'`, so 30-min review timeouts
    and 90-min fix timeouts (likely modes for Claude API stalls)
    showed up as `'cancelled'` and were silenced.
  - Item 6 in the review: the trigger step computed `BRANCH` from the
    runner clock, which drifts vs. Claude's branch when the fix step
    crosses 00:00 UTC, producing a 404 the old script silently mapped
    to "Skipped".

Fix:
- Add `notify-workflow-failure.sh` that opens a tracking GitHub issue
  using only the built-in GITHUB_TOKEN — no extra secrets needed for
  out-of-the-box alerting. README still documents the Slack swap.
- Add `determine-area` to `notify.needs` and broaden the condition to
  treat both `failure` and `cancelled` as alertable across all three
  upstream jobs.
- Compute the branch name once (`steps.branch.outputs.name`),
  interpolate it into Claude's prompt (so Claude pushes the exact
  expected ref), and reuse the same value in the trigger step. The
  date is computed exactly once — no clock-drift window.

Addresses items 4, 5, 6 from review issue: review(error-handling):
findings — 2026-05-10.

